Subject: Re: [T2] crankshaft--removing dist. drive gear

On 6/16/05 5:15 PM, "Dave Horrigan" <dave(-at-)horrigania.karoo.co.uk> wrote:

> On 16/6/05 7:11 pm, "jenny" <jboothbee(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
> 
>> Anyone have any tips on how to
>> press the gear off?  Type I engine.
> 
> You can use a 3-arm gear puller for this if you don't have a hole in the
> press bed.  Just pull both gears off together.


Most 3-arm pullers will not be able to grab the gear because there is very
little space between the gear and the cheek of the crankshaft.

If you have a press, try getting some pieces of 1/8" steel plate to put on
top of the press blocks, it might work.


